<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fans Will See A Lot of McGwire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Even though Mark McGwire has at least 10 fewer home runs than  
last year, there will still be plenty of Big Mac on Fox. 
</P>
<P>
	When the network picked up its coverage last season on May 30,  
McGwire already had hit 25 homers. He'll be well short of that when 
the network makes its season debut Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	But that doesn't matter.  
</P>
<P>
	Fox will still give viewers live look-ins to as many of  
McGwire's at-bats as possible in 1999 -- as well as those of Sammy 
Sosa, Ken Griffey Jr., Jose Canseco -- and anyone else in pursuit of 
breaking McGwire's home run mark. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were very fortunate last year to go live many times and be  
able to capture many of McGwire, Sosa and Junior's home runs,'' 
said Fox executive producer Ed Goren. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox's schedule couldn't begin any better. The first two weekends  
feature interleague play, including the Yankees-Mets at 1 p.m. EDT 
on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is, by far, the best schedule we've had in the four years  
since I've been here,'' said Tim McCarver, Fox's top analyst who 
will work the New York game. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yankees-Mets matchup will hold a special meaning for  
McCarver. It will be his first Mets game since the team fired him 
before the start of this season after 16 years as the club's 
broadcaster. McCarver was picked up by George Steinbrenner and the 
Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
	It will take a near-miracle to duplicate the fan interest last  
season when McGwire and Sosa made their assaults on Roger Maris' 
home run mark and Fox's ratings jumped a record 15 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The increase was the largest jump for baseball's game of the  
week television package in more than 30 years. 
</P>
<P>
	However, with all the home runs being hit this season, ESPN's  
ratings are the same as last year. 
</P>
<P>
	``Did baseball exhaust its fans last year?'' McCarver said. ``I  
don't think so. ... If I were going to say anybody who may break 
McGwire's record, I'd have to say (Griffey) Junior.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McCarver, who has never been afraid to express his opinions said  
the mound should be raised to give pitchers an advantage. 
</P>
<P>
	``They ought to raise it five inches,'' McCarver said, ``like  
they did after the 1968 season when Carl Yastrzemski was the only 
.300 hitter in all of baseball.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Although Fox's coverage won't alter much from last year -- it  
will keep ``Catcher-Cam'' and microphones on managers and in bases 
-- its pregame will have a different look. 
</P>
<P>
	Keith Olbermann will join Steve Lyons for ``In the Zone,'' the  
30-minute feature show that targets the young male audience. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *REPLAY:* As usual, Fox's top broadcasting team of McCarver and  
Joe Buck are on the same page about keeping instant replay as far 
away from baseball as possible. 
</P>
<P>
	``The second it happened, the game came to a screeching halt,  
became sloppy and took forever,'' said Buck, who worked the radio 
broadcast for Monday's Florida-St. Louis game in which umpire Frank 
Pulli decided to view a videotape replay and change a home run to a 
double. 
</P>
<P>
	``Can you imagine having every ball and strike argued and go  
into instant replay?'' McCarver said. ``It would be muddled. My 
vote is a very convincing no.'' 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *BETTER LATE THAN NEVER:* After poor weather prevented ABC from  
using its ``Gyro Cam'' for the Kentucky Derby, the network has the 
go-ahead to employ it for Saturday's Belmont Stakes. 
</P>
<P>
	The camera is mounted on a vehicle that follows the horses along  
the inside of the track, and is expected to give viewers low camera 
angles that have never been seen in a horse race before. 
</P>
<P>
	For the third straight year, ABC should have an increased  
audience with the possibility of a Triple Crown winner. There will 
be a record 37 cameras, including two isolation cameras on 
Charismatic. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *TUBE BITS:* ABC airs a two-hour special on the century's  
greatest games Saturday at 2:30 p.m. EDT and the U.S. women's 
national soccer team's final tune-up against Canada on Sunday at 2 
p.m. ... Roy Jones Jr. fights Reggie Johnson in a light-heavyweight 
unification title fight Saturday at 9:30 p.m. on HBO. ... Sunday's 
Eastern Conference finals Game 1 posted a 7.5 overnight rating, 
while the Indianapolis 500 had a 5.3 mark. ... ESPN's Steve Cyphers 
was host for the national spelling bee Thursday at noon and then 
traveled to New York for Saturday's Belmont Stakes. ... ABC will 
use the first-down yellow line for this year's ``Monday Night 
Football'' telecasts and the Super Bowl. 
  	   	
</P>
