	Rockies 3, Braves 2, 11 Innings  
</P>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Todd Helton hit a solo homer in the 11th inning  
last night to give the Colorado Rockies a 3-2 victory over the 
Atlanta Braves. Helton, who entered the game in the ninth inning as 
a pinch-hitter, connected on a 1-2 pitch for his 10th home run of 
the season, a shot over the right-field fence off Russ Springer. 

</P>
