<HEADLINE> Clash 4, Rapids 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Jeff Baicher, Ronald Cerritos and  
Mauricio Wright scored in the final 17 minutes to give the San Jose 
Clash a 4-3 victory over the Colorado Rapids in Major League Soccer 
play Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	With Colorado trailing 3-1 midway through the second half,  
Baicher, who also had two assists, took a touch pass from Dario 
Brose from 20 yards out and curled a shot past a diving Marcus 
Hahnemann in the 73rd minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Four minutes later, Cerritos headed a crossing pass from Eddie  
Lewis to tie it. Wright netted the game-winner in the 80th minute 
from in close off a corner kick. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis opened the scoring in the third minute, but Colorado took  
a 2-1 lead at halftime on goals by Ross Paule and Paul Bravo. 
Anders Limpar extended the lead to 3-1 in the 69th minute. 
  	   	
