<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Mostly Up; Dow Gains 38.31 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Prices were mostly higher on Wall Street today  
as the modest rally that lifted technology stocks late Wednesday 
spread to blue-chips. 
</P>
<P>
	At 11 a.m. EDT, the Dow Jones industrial average was up 38.31 at  
10,616.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500  
index was up 3.81 at 1,298.62, and the Nasdaq composite index was 
down 5.35 at 2,427.06. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wednesday, the Dow closed 18.37 lower at 10,577.89, but other  
market indicators rose as investors began seeking bargains. 
Technology stocks that have been battered over the past few weeks 
were snapped up at their new, lower prices. 
</P>
<P>
	Today, however, the volatile Internet companies led the  
technology sector right back down. Amazon.com fell 2 15/16 to 109 
3/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Otherwise, gains were broad-based, with Johnson &AMP; Johnson, up 1  
7/16 at 93 1/8, leading the Dow components. 
</P>
<P>
	The nation's biggest retailers were mostly higher after  
stronger-than-expected sales in May indicated that Americans are 
still ready and willing to spend money. Wal-Mart rose 1 1/8 to 45 1/2 and 
Gap Inc. rose 2 7/8 to 65 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
	Chevron rose 1 15/16 to 93 15/16 and Texaco fell 9/16 to 63  
15/16 after the companies called off merger talks. 
</P>
<P>
	The market is waiting for the Friday morning release of the  
Labor Department's unemployment data. Traders are especially 
interested in the wage component of the report, which could offer 
the latest indication of whether inflation has returned to the U.S. 
economy -- and whether the Federal Reserve will raise interest rates 
when its Open Market Committee meets later this month. 
</P>
<P>
	Today, a separate report showed the number of Americans filing  
new claims for unemployment benefits rose last week, but only a 
slight 4,000 to 305,000. That level is still considered extremely 
low unemployment. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin on the  
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 228.6 million shares, 
slightly ahead of Wednesday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was up 2.06 at 622.56, and the American  
Stock Exchange composite index was up 2.44 at 773.67. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
