<HEADLINE> Albright Cancels Mexico Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright on  
Thursday canceled her trip to Mexico following Yugoslavia's 
reported acceptance of a peace plan for Kosovo. 
</P>
<P>
	Albright was to have headed a high-level interagency delegation  
for talks with Mexican officials on cross border issues. 
</P>
<P>
	Attorney General Janet Reno will lead the U.S. delegation in  
place of Albright. 
</P>
<P>
	State Department spokesman James P. Rubin said Albright  
expressed regret over her absence to Mexican Foreign Secretary 
Rosario Green. He said Albright will visit Mexico later. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
