<HEADLINE> Ex-Boyfriend Arrested for Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- A former boyfriend was accused Thursday of stabbing  
a woman who staggered from door to door, pleading for help, before 
she died in a driveway in Miami's Little Haiti neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
	Anthony Gary Ferguson was charged with second degree murder in  
the May 24 death of Portia Lee, 30, a mother of six who left a 
trail of blood for 100 yards before she collapsed. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said Ms. Lee was visiting a friend in the neighborhood  
and Ferguson caught up with her in the middle of the street after 
she left the friend's home. A handful of people watched the attack, 
but did nothing, police said. Someone eventually called 911. 
</P>
<P>
	``Not only did people watch her get beaten up, they likely  
watched her get stabbed,'' Lt. Bill Schwartz said. 
</P>
<P>
	He said anyone who saw the attack would be treated as a witness  
and would not face charges for failing to assist Ms. Lee. 
</P>
<P>
	Ferguson had been arrested twice since March for domestic  
violence against Ms. Lee and she was in the process of obtaining a 
restraining order against him, Schwartz said. 
</P>
<P>
	The maximum sentence for second degree murder is life in prison.  
  	   	
</P>
