<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 16:00:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Against GOP Budget Proposals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Setting the stage for a budget fight,  
President Clinton on Thursday said GOP spending plans were ``a 
blueprint for chaos'' and failed to shore up the Social Security 
and Medicare systems. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton, appearing in the Rose Garden after meeting with his  
Cabinet, said his budget would address the fiscal problems of both 
Social Security and Medicare while honoring mandated spending caps 
and investing in education and the environment. 
</P>
<P>
	``Unfortunately, the Republican majority in Congress is moving  
ahead with a budget plan that, in the end, may do none of these 
things,'' Clinton said. ``It fails to extend the solvency of Social 
Security and Medicare. It fails to make new, crucial investments.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton also said the GOP plans called for cuts ``in areas of  
great national need -- from law enforcement, to education, to the 
environment.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``The majority budget plan is simply not realistic,'' the  
president said. ``It is a blueprint for chaos and we can do 
better.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
