<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Illnois School District in Turmoil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VENICE, Ill. (AP) -- When teachers complain about outrageous  
behavior, they're often talking about their students. In Venice, 
they're talking about their boss. 
</P>
<P>
	Since taking over last fall, Superintendent James Doughty has  
been sued for harassment, chastised for locking out students, 
charged with illegally withholding teachers' paychecks and accused 
of pressuring a principal to give bad evaluations to union 
teachers. 
</P>
<P>
	In March, police were called to a raucous school board meeting  
in this small community northeast of St. Louis to escort the 
superintendent to his car as angry parents shouted ``Doughty's got 
to go!'' 
</P>
<P>
	All of this in a district that ranks near the bottom of Illinois  
schools in student achievement, and where teachers say some 
classrooms went without books all year despite state funds to help 
troubled schools. 
</P>
<P>
	Doughty ``needs to go,'' said Ann Mullins, an elementary school  
teacher in Venice. ``There's nothing this district can do as long 
as he's here.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Doughty has declined repeatedly to comment on the allegations.  
In March, he said the controversy doesn't mean he lacks community 
support. 
</P>
<P>
	Allegations against Doughty continued to build on Wednesday when  
the school board learned about dozens of union grievances filed 
since he took office. They include accusations that Doughty has 
refused to meet with union leaders over labor complaints and has 
improperly laid off, demoted and transferred employees. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm still in awe,'' school board Vice President Metro Pierson  
after reviewing the complaints. 
</P>
<P>
	In February, Doughty was criticized for locking out high school  
students who staged a walkout to protest the suspension of a 
popular principal. Doughty had punished the principal for missing a 
bathroom inspection. 
</P>
<P>
	In March, Madison County prosecutors filed misdemeanor charges  
against Doughty, accusing him of illegally withholding the 
paychecks of five teachers who failed to check in with him 
following an education conference. 
</P>
<P>
	And last week, Venice Elementary School Principal Rachelle Artis  
wrote school board members alleging Doughty pressured her to file 
negative evaluations of three teachers who serve on the board of 
the teacher's union. 
</P>
<P>
	School board member Tyrone Echols said he will work to close a  
split in the board that has produced a narrow majority in favor of 
Doughty throughout the year. 
</P>
<P>
	``The board needs to come together and realize he is destructive  
to our community,'' he said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
