<HEADLINE> Shore Named News Editor in Denver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Sandy Shore, a newswoman for The Associated Press  
in Denver since 1987, has been promoted to news editor. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced today by Denver Chief of Bureau  
Peter Mattiace. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Shore, 43, is a native of Miami, Ariz., and a journalism  
graduate of the University of Arizona at Tucson. She worked for 
several weeklies and the daily Casa Grande (Ariz.) Dispatch. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Shore joined the AP in Phoenix in 1985. She moved to the  
Denver bureau two years later and has covered the Oklahoma City 
bombing trials, the JonBenet Ramsey investigation in Boulder and 
the Columbine High School massacre in Littleton. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
