<HEADLINE> Detroit Police Station Evacuated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Detroit police headquarters was evacuated briefly  
Thursday after a suspicious-looking briefcase was found in a van 
brought to the department. 
</P>
<P>
	The bomb squad took the briefcase to police property nearby  
where it was ``opened carefully,'' Officer Claude Fox said. 
</P>
<P>
	Some wiring was found inside, but the bomb squad would not  
immediately say whether any explosives were found, Fox said. 
</P>
<P>
	The briefcase, which was suspiciously taped, was found in a van  
that was brought to the department around 4 p.m. People were 
ordered out for about 10 minutes. The van is suspected of being 
used in a string of robberies. 
  	   	
</P>
