<HEADLINE> Five Dead After Interstate Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSON, Tenn. (AP) -- A truck drifted off the highway, jumped an  
embankment and crashed on top of an oxygen tanker Thursday, 
exploding the tanker and killing five people. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was just like a bomb going off,'' said Albert Hart of  
Canton, Ohio. ``There were 75 feet of flames that went up in a 
mushroom cloud and black smoke so thick you couldn't see through 
it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Police said the driver of a Ryder tractor-trailer apparently  
fell asleep at the wheel, and his truck drifted off the side of 
Interstate 40 west near a rest area where other trucks were parked. 
</P>
<P>
	The truck hit a depression, then jumped off an embankment and  
landed on top of an oxygen tanker. The tanker exploded, throwing 
the Ryder truck into an 18-wheeler, which in turn struck another 
tractor-trailer. 
</P>
<P>
	Both the Ryder and tanker trucks were destroyed in the fire. Two  
people died in each truck. It was unclear which truck the fifth 
fatality was in. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
